<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1868,2037]" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">
The single described species in this genus remains known only from Honshu, 
<collectingCountry box="[1024,1091,1869,1892]" name="Japan" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">Japan</collectingCountry>
, where it was recorded from at least five different genera of plants, most of which are members of the 
<taxonomicName box="[967,1053,1904,1929]" class="Magnoliopsida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="order">Fagales</taxonomicName>
or even 
<taxonomicName box="[1156,1264,1905,1929]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Fagaceae</taxonomicName>
. The species is unusual within the 
<taxonomicName box="[371,504,1940,1964]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Scirtothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[371,504,1940,1964]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">Scirtothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
genus-group in having the pronotal sculpture weak with widely spaced lines, the mesonotal submedian setae arising close to the posterior margin, the tergites with few rows of microtrichia, and the antennae are 
<number box="[299,312,2012,2037]" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" value="7.0">7</number>
-segmented.
</paragraph>
